==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Typical
<hw>Typ"ic*al</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>typicus</ets>, Gr. <?/, from <?/ type: cf. F. <ets>typique</ets>.
See <er>Type</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Of the nature of a type;
representing something by a form, model, or resemblance; emblematic;
prefigurative.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The Levitical priesthood was only <qex>typical</qex> of the
Christian.</q> <rj><qau>Atterbury.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Nat. Hist.)</fld> <def>Combining or exhibiting the
essential characteristics of a group; <as>as, a <ex>typical</ex>
genus</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p>-- <wordforms><wf>Typ"ic*al*ly</wf>, <pos>adv.</pos> --
<wf>Typ"ic*al*ness</wf>, <pos>n.</pos></wordforms>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Typification</ent>⟦br⟧
